The indefinite integral of ln(x) * sin(x) is ln(x) * cos(x) - x * sin(x). Substituting 'x=4' into this result, we get ln(4) * cos(4) - 4 * sin(4), which equals 1.69897737776. Rounding down, we get 1.

The indefinite integral of 5 * (ln(x) * sin(x)) is 5 * (cos(x) * ln(x) - sin(x) * x). Substituting 'x=4' into this result, we get 5 * (cos(4) * ln(4) - sin(4) * 4), which equals 32.5639375. Rounding down, we get 32.
